bins = np.arange(0, 101, 5)
bin_width = np.diff(bins)[0]
xtick_positions = bins[:-1] + bin_width/2
xtick_labels = [f"{bins[i]}-{bins[i+1]}" for i in range(len(bins)-1)]

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 8))
counts, bin_edges, patches = plt.hist(instalacions[instalacions['Potència'] <= 100]['Potència'], bins=bins)
bin_centers = (bin_edges[:-1] + bin_edges[1:]) / 2
plt.xticks(xtick_positions, xtick_labels, rotation=45)
plt.xlabel('Potència (kWp)', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Nombre instal·lacions', fontsize=14)
plt.title('Histograma', fontsize=18, fontweight='bold')

for i in range(len(counts)):

    bin_center = bin_centers[i]
    ax.annotate(str(count), xy=(bin_center, count), xytext=(0, 5), textcoords='offset points', ha='center', fontsize=12)

# Group the installations by comarca and type
counts = instalacions.groupby(['Comarca', 'Tecnologia'])['Tecnologia'].count().unstack().fillna(0)

# Define the symbol shapes and colors for each installation type
symbols = {'FOTOVOLTAICA': 'o', 'COGENERACIO': 's', 'BIOGÀS': '^', 'HIDROELECTRICA': 'd', 'ENERGIES RESIDUALS': '*', 'RESIDUS': 'X'}
colors = {'FOTOVOLTAICA': '#3CB371', 'COGENERACIO': '#FFA500', 'BIOGÀS': '#6A5ACD', 'HIDROELECTRICA': '#87CEFA', 'ENERGIES RESIDUALS': '#FF69B4', 'RESIDUS': '#FF0000'}

# Create the plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20, 10))

# Iterate over each comarca and plot the symbols for each installation type
for i, comarca in enumerate(counts.index):
    row = counts.loc[comarca]
    for j, col in enumerate(row.index):
        count = row[col]
        if count > 0:
            x = i
            y = j
            symbol = symbols[col]
            color = colors[col]
            ax.scatter(x, y, s=100*count, marker=symbol, color=color, edgecolors='k', linewidths=1, alpha=0.7)

# Set the axis labels and title
ax.set_xticks(np.arange(len(counts)))
ax.set_xticklabels(counts.index, rotation=90)
ax.set_yticks(np.arange(len(counts.columns)))
ax.set_yticklabels(counts.columns)
ax.set_xlabel('Comarca')
ax.set_ylabel('Tipus d\'instal·lació')
ax.set_title('Isotype chart de les instal·lacions per comarca')

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# Define icons
icons = {
    'FOTOVOLTAICA': './icons/icon1.png',
    'COGENERACIO': './icons/icon2.png',
    'BIOGÀS': './icons/icon3.png',
    'HIDROELECTRICA': './icons/icon4.png',
    'ENERGIES RESIDUALS': './icons/icon5.png',
    'RESIDUS': './icons/icon6.png'
}

# Define function to add icons to chart
def add_icon(ax, x, y, icon_path):
    icon_size = 0.03  # adjust icon size as needed
    img = plt.imread(icon_path)
    im = OffsetImage(img, zoom=icon_size)
    im.image.axes = ax
    ab = AnnotationBbox(im, (x, y), xycoords='data', frameon=False)
    ax.add_artist(ab)

# Create isotype chart
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
comarcas = instalacions['Comarca'].unique()
for comarca in comarcas:
    comarca_data = instalacions[instalacions['Comarca'] == comarca]
    y = np.arange(len(comarca_data))
    icons_paths = [icons[tecnologia] for tecnologia in comarca_data['Tecnologia']]
    ax.scatter(comarca_data['Comarca'], y, s=100, alpha=0.7)
    for i, (x, y) in enumerate(zip(comarca_data['Comarca'], y)):
        add_icon(ax, x, y, icons_paths[i])
ax.set_yticks(np.arange(len(instalacions)))
ax.set_yticklabels(instalacions['Municipi'].tolist())
ax.set_xticks(comarcas)
ax.set_xticklabels(comarcas, rotation=90)
ax.set_title('Instalacions per comarca i tipus d\'energia')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Define icon codes and labels
icon_codes = {
    'FOTOVOLTAICA': '\uf185',
    'COGENERACIO': '\uf0f4',
    'BIOGÀS': '\uf1e1',
    'HIDROELECTRICA': '\uf0e5',
    'ENERGIES RESIDUALS': '\uf2e2',
    'RESIDUS': '\uf1ae'
}
icon_labels = list(icon_codes.keys())

# Define a palette for the comarques
comarca_palette = sns.color_palette("pastel", n_colors=len(instalacions['Comarca'].unique()))

# Create figure and axes
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))

# Loop through each comarca and plot the icons
for i, (comarca, data) in enumerate(instalacions.groupby('Comarca')):
    x_offset = 0
    for j, (tipus_instalacio, group) in enumerate(data.groupby('Tecnologia')):
        num_instalacions = len(group)
        for k in range(num_instalacions):
            # Plot the icon
            ax.text(i + x_offset, k, icon_codes[tipus_instalacio], fontfamily='FontAwesome', 
                    fontsize=20, ha='center', va='center', color=comarca_palette[i])
        # Update the x_offset for the next icon
        x_offset += 0.25
        
# Set axis labels and title
ax.set_xlabel('Comarca')
ax.set_ylabel('Instal·lacions')
ax.set_title('Distribució de les instal·lacions per comarca i tipus')

# Set the xticks and xtick labels
xtick_labels = list(instalacions['Comarca'].unique())
ax.set_xticks(range(len(xtick_labels)))
ax.set_xticklabels(xtick_labels, rotation=45, ha='right')

# Set the yticks and ytick labels
ytick_labels = [''] * len(instalacions)
ytick_labels[::len(icon_labels)] = icon_labels
ax.set_yticks(range(len(instalacions)))
ax.set_yticklabels(ytick_labels)

# Add a legend for the comarques
handles = [plt.Rectangle((0,0),1,1, color=comarca_palette[i], ec='black') 
           for i in range(len(xtick_labels))]
ax.legend(handles, xtick_labels, loc='upper left')

# Remove the spines
sns.despine(left=True, bottom=True)

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# Define icon codes and labels
icon_dict = {
    'FOTOVOLTAICA': '\uf185',
    'COGENERACIO': '\uf0f4',
    'BIOGÀS': '\uf1e1',
    'HIDROELECTRICA': '\uf0e5',
    'ENERGIES RESIDUALS': '\uf2e2',
    'RESIDUS': '\uf1ae'
}

# Define a function to download an icon from Font Awesome given its name
def get_icon_image(icon_name):
    url = f"https://fontawesome.com/icons/{icon_name}?style=solid"
    response = requests.get(url)
    img = Image.open(BytesIO(response.content))
    return img

# Create a list of icon images for each type of installation
icon_images = [get_icon_image(icon_dict[instalacio]) for instalacio in instalacions["Tecnologia"]]

# Define a function to resize an image to a given width while maintaining aspect ratio
def resize_image(img, new_width):
    aspect_ratio = img.size[1] / img.size[0]
    new_height = int(new_width * aspect_ratio)
    return img.resize((new_width, new_height))

# Resize all the icon images to have the same width
icon_width = 50
icon_images_resized = [resize_image(img, icon_width) for img in icon_images]



# Create a figure and axis object
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))

# Plot each icon image at the corresponding position
for i, img in enumerate(icon_images_resized):
    ab = AnnotationBbox(OffsetImage(img), (0, i), frameon=False)
    ax.add_artist(ab)

# Set the xticks and xtick labels
ax.set_xticks([])
ax.set_xticklabels([])

# Set the yticks and ytick labels
ytick_labels = [icon_dict[instalacio] for instalacio in instalacions["Tecnologia"]]
ytick_labels = np.repeat(ytick_labels, 1)
ax.set_yticks(range(len(instalacions)))
ax.set_yticklabels(ytick_labels, fontsize=20)

        
# Set the title and axis labels
ax.set_title("Número d'instal·lacions per comarca i tipus", fontsize=24)
ax.set_xlabel("Comarca", fontsize=20)
ax.set_ylabel("Tipus d'instal·lació", fontsize=20)


# Remove the spines
sns.despine(left=True, bottom=True)

# Show the plot
plt.show()
